        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued April 2 at 2:35PM EDT until April 2 at 2:45PM EDT by NWS Pittsburgh PA</headline>
        <description>At 235 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Mount
Pleasant, or 10 miles northeast of Connellsville, moving east at 65
mph.

HAZARD...Quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.

Locations impacted include...
Mount Pleasant, Scottdale, New Stanton, Calumet-Norvelt, Everson,
Hunker, Donegal, Acme and Jones Mills.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. This storm is capable of producing large hail.</instruction>
